1
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,679
<i>At the start, you had my heart, oh</i>

2
00:00:12,762 --> 00:00:14,597
<i>You are my everything</i>

3
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:17,058
<i>Attracted to my light, poor thing</i>

4
00:00:17,142 --> 00:00:18,476
<i>Ugh, boring!</i>

5
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:22,105
<i>I can't retain, don't say my name</i>
<i>'Cause I'm your only claim to fame</i>

6
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:24,232
<i>I'm too smart, too hard</i>
<i>Too busy, too pretty</i>

7
00:00:24,315 --> 00:00:25,650
<i>To get caught up in…</i>

8
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:27,944
Uh, Kitty Song-Covey. I'm on the list.

9
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:32,323
Afraid not.

10
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:35,618
No, I have to be. That's my boyfriend.

11
00:00:36,995 --> 00:00:39,039
Uh-huh, I'm sure it is.

12
00:00:39,539 --> 00:00:40,915
I'm not lying.

13
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:42,125
Min Ho!

14
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,627
Look, sorry, I can't let you in.

15
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:46,421
Especially not in that.

16
00:00:52,427 --> 00:00:54,137
<i>All the boys wanna see me</i>

17
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,723
<i>All the girls wanna be me</i>

18
00:00:56,806 --> 00:00:58,975
<i>It ain't surprising</i>

19
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,727
<i>I'm hypnotizing</i>

20
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:03,980
<i>I get them so excited with a kiss</i>

21
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:06,733
Hey. You were having a nightmare.

22
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:10,195
Yeah, I guess I was.

23
00:01:10,278 --> 00:01:13,531
I love interpreting bad dreams.
Were you falling from the sky?

24
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,283
Naked in front of a class?

25
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,160
Ooh. Losing all your teeth?

26
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:19,829
Min Ho and Eunice
were making out in front of me.

27
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:24,918
Okay, it gets really dark
inside that bubbly brain of yours.

28
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:28,129
Well, last night, Min Ho said
he was going out with Marius,

29
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:30,423
but then I saw him
sneaking off with Eunice.

30
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:31,591
And they were hugging.

31
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:34,594
And not like a hello-goodbye hug.
It lingered.

32
00:01:34,677 --> 00:01:38,056
Kitty, there's no way.
He's her manager. They work together.

33
00:01:38,139 --> 00:01:40,183
And people hug all the time.

34
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:43,686
And besides, Min Ho's a great guy,
and he is obsessed with you.

35
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:45,021
Just trust him.

36
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,649
You're right. I know you're right.

37
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:51,861
Oh my God! It's Yisoo.
Like, the actual Yisoo.

38
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:55,406
She wants me to meet her at the office,
like, right now. Right now.

39
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,117
- Gotta hurry! Okay…
- It's Chuseok.

40
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,369
Don't you have, like, time off the clock?

41
00:01:59,452 --> 00:02:02,247
You don't get to be a fashion legend
by taking holidays off.

42
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:04,332
Oh my God, this is amazing.

43
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:07,585
I didn't even know she knew my name.
I've never even met her before.

44
00:02:07,669 --> 00:02:09,504
Well, I'm very glad she sees you,

45
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:12,257
but you are gonna make it
to Dae's dad's restaurant, right?

46
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:14,050
My <i>imo-halmoni's </i>coming from Bukjeon.

47
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:17,428
This might be my last chance to have
traditional Chuseok with friends and fam.

48
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:21,349
Yes, of course.
I will not miss Dae's grand opening.

49
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:22,892
Save me a seat, okay?

50
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:29,399
Kitty, don't spiral.

51
00:02:29,899 --> 00:02:31,526
Go talk to your boyfriend.

52
00:02:38,616 --> 00:02:40,451
{\an8}HAVE A GREAT CHUSEOK

53
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:54,465
- Kitty! Hey, hey.
- Morning! You're glowing.

54
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:57,510
Oh, well, that's probably
my 13-step Korean skincare routine,

55
00:02:57,594 --> 00:03:01,055
or the fact that
Jin and I said "I love you" last night.

56
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,765
Stop! Tell me everything!

57
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:05,310
Okay. If you must know,
I usually start with a cleansing oil.

58
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:07,061
- Then I'll go in with salicylic--
- Q?

59
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:09,397
I don't know.
We didn't plan it or anything.

60
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,982
We just kind of blurted it out.

61
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:13,276
That is so romantic.

62
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:16,362
Wait, so this means you got over
your little episode of <i>Q's Anatomy</i>

63
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:18,239
in the summer with Marius?

64
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:21,409
Oh, yeah. Water under the bridge.

65
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,745
Marius is ancient history.

66
00:03:23,828 --> 00:03:27,081
Although he did tell me last night that
I was the reason he came back to KISS.

67
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:29,334
I know. Intense.

68
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:31,336
Damn, does that change anything?

69
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:35,673
If it did, would I be introducing Jin
to Dr. Candelaria?

70
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:38,468
Wait, whoa! Your love life is,
like, popping off right now.

71
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:40,553
I know. I'm kind of nervous.

72
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,555
I never introduced my mom
to my boyfriends.

73
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:44,724
She's always got high standards.

74
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:48,186
Well, I'm sure when she sees
how in love you two are,

75
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:49,562
she'll be nothing but supportive.

76
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:54,192
I hope so. God, look at us.
Happy, mature relationships.

77
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:56,277
Yes! You and me both!

78
00:03:56,361 --> 00:03:57,362
See you later.

79
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,740
<i>What am I going to say?</i>
<i>Keep it cool, Kitty.</i>

80
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,617
<i>"Where </i>were <i>you last night?"</i>

81
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,369
"Where <i>were you last night?"</i>

82
00:04:04,452 --> 00:04:06,496
<i>"Where were </i>you <i>last night?"</i>

83
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:12,543
Oh my God!

84
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:16,297
So sorry, Eunice.

85
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:20,593
Didn't mean to… do that.

86
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:25,974
Just set you right here.

87
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:28,142
My God, that is lifelike.

88
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:34,649
<i>Okay, this is actually weirder</i>
<i>than my nightmare.</i>

89
00:04:38,987 --> 00:04:40,113
Are you stalking me, Covey?

90
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:42,657
I'm actually looking
for the Eunice Museum.

91
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:45,285
Ha-ha, very funny. Hey.

92
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:50,873
Um, how was it with Marius last night?

93
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,794
Yeah, about that, um…

94
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:58,214
I didn't actually end up
going out with him.

95
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:00,675
Because you were with Eunice?

96
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,803
I saw you two from my window.

97
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,763
Okay, the truth is…

98
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:09,684
I didn't want you
to figure out our secret.

99
00:05:10,184 --> 00:05:13,855
I was getting her opinion
on whether or not you'd like…

100
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:16,274
this.

101
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:19,777
Happy Chuseok, Covey.

102
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:26,492
- The gift is actually inside the box.
- Right. No, no. Of course.

103
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:32,707
It's beautiful.

104
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:34,167
I'm sorry for the white lie.

105
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,627
You're just such a hard person
to surprise.

106
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,588
I don't know what to say.

107
00:05:38,671 --> 00:05:41,049
I think of Chuseok
as an anniversary for us.

108
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:43,843
It's when I started
having feelings for you.

109
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:51,893
So…

110
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:55,897
What are you doing here?

111
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:59,025
Oh, I, um…

112
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:01,069
I need your help.

113
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:05,531
Jiwon texted me and said
that Imo-Halmoni canceled on tonight.

114
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:07,408
I'm so sorry.

115
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:10,620
Yeah. At the very least,
I want to call her and say happy Chuseok.

116
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:12,914
And my Korean is getting better, but…

117
00:06:12,997 --> 00:06:14,540
All right, say no more.

118
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:17,210
Remember? Soon Ja-<i>nim </i>adores me.

119
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:19,587
Thank you.

120
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:28,179
Yisoo, it's such an honor to meet you.

121
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:31,724
Well, everyone has already left
for the Chuseok holiday.

122
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:36,145
To be honest, I'd usually give this task
to a more experienced person.

123
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:38,356
Oh, well. Desperate times.

124
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:41,484
I can handle anything.
Just leave it to me.

125
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:42,610
Good.

126
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:44,987
Ah.

127
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,573
Koko's sitter canceled.

128
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:49,450
I'll be back in three days.

129
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,702
But Koko has separation anxiety,

130
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,246
so don't ever leave him alone.

131
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:55,039
Keep giving him verbal affirmation.

132
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:58,418
Oh, and never make direct eye contact.

133
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,754
Oh, and he's vegan. Mm!

134
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:05,216
Aren't you a little angel, Koko? Mwah!

135
00:07:05,299 --> 00:07:06,300
Do well!

136
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:08,511
Impress me. And who knows?

137
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:11,597
Maybe one day
you'll become my second assistant.

138
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,350
Koko, Mommy's leaving! Be good.

139
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:15,560
Bye!

140
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:19,355
What are you doing? Bring down my bag.

141
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,356
Chop-chop!

142
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,524
Uh…

143
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:26,571
Oh my God!

144
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:44,255
You came.

145
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:46,674
- Welcome to BoDaeGa.
- Thank you.

146
00:07:46,757 --> 00:07:48,509
I thought of the name.

147
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:50,845
It's mine, my brother's
and my mom's put together.

148
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:54,515
Wow, Bora, you've grown so much!
What happened?

149
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:55,892
Yuri! Welcome!

150
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:58,186
Hello, Mr. Kim. Congratulations.

151
00:07:58,269 --> 00:07:59,562
Thank you.

152
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:06,527
It's because of your family
we were able to open. I feel a little…

153
00:08:06,611 --> 00:08:08,738
Oh, there’s really no reason
to feel any way.

154
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,615
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

155
00:08:10,698 --> 00:08:12,909
- Yes!
- I'll do it. Stay here and talk.

156
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,957
- Huh?
- Ah.

157
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:22,710
You got a dog?

158
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:24,212
It's my boss's.

159
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,923
I had to bring him
because he can't be left alone.

160
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:30,176
How could you bring a dog here
when we just passed a health inspection?

161
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:31,511
We could be shut down.

162
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:34,514
Sorry. I didn't think of that. I'll go.

163
00:08:34,597 --> 00:08:37,225
No, Dae, you can't uninvite her!

164
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:38,601
And he's so cute!

165
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,144
Don't make eye contact.

166
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:41,187
Okay, fine.

167
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,940
Just promise me
you'll keep him out of sight.

168
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,816
Of course. Of course.

169
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:50,571
- I said, "I'll do it myself."
- Mom, don't.

170
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:52,323
I snapped that ankle back into place

171
00:08:52,406 --> 00:08:55,368
with my hands
in the middle of a Thai jungle.

172
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:58,204
I'll never forget that guy's scream.

173
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:01,249
- I'll never forget that story.
- This bitch is sick.

174
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:02,917
My injury was more of a sprain.

175
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,003
Luckily, I didn't need surgery
because I'm also a screamer.

176
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:08,548
Huh.

177
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,550
Marius!

178
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:14,136
Dr. Candelaria!
I didn't know you were coming for Chuseok.

179
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,305
Oh, you must join us. Sit.

180
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:23,145
When Quincy first came to KISS,
he was so homesick until he met this one.

181
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:24,855
They were inseparable.

182
00:09:24,939 --> 00:09:29,610
It was such a relief, especially after all
the trouble Q had at elementary school.

183
00:09:29,694 --> 00:09:32,113
- Mom, please stop.
- He had to wear an eye patch.

184
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:33,698
I mean, his dad used to say,

185
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:37,410
"He really puts the 'lazy'
in the 'lazy eye.'"

186
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,787
- I'm sure it was very cute.
- It was not.

187
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:42,415
Well, actually, I have a photo.

188
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:44,333
- Check this.
- Oh no, we don't have to…

189
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,251
Look at that.

190
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:46,961
- Okay, there it is.
- Bam.

191
00:09:47,044 --> 00:09:48,170
So good.

192
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:53,926
I'm sorry.

193
00:09:54,802 --> 00:09:56,721
Look at this place. It's perfect.

194
00:09:57,221 --> 00:10:01,017
It has to be. My dad sank
most of the settlement money into this.

195
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,478
Well, this is gonna be a huge success.
You have nothing to worry about.

196
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:05,396
Thanks.

197
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:07,398
Min Ho! Is Eunice coming?

198
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:11,277
Ah, she's going to be spending
the holiday with her family.

199
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:19,285
- Um, is everyone here?
- Actually, we're waiting on one more.

200
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:20,328
We are?

201
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:25,750
I don't think I can handle another setup
with Professor Vegemite.

202
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:29,003
No, no. I think you're gonna like
tonight's surprise a lot more.

203
00:10:29,086 --> 00:10:32,965
Ta-da! Happy Chuseok!

204
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,468
I convinced her to come after all.

205
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:36,510
Halmoni…

206
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:40,514
You wouldn't come home to me,
so I had to come to you.

207
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:43,601
Hello.

208
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:45,102
Yes, yes.

209
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:48,022
Let's go.

210
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:52,610
What is going on?

211
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:56,113
The reason I said Halmoni couldn't come
is because I didn't invite her.

212
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,657
What? Why not?

213
00:10:57,740 --> 00:11:00,284
She didn't approve of me moving to Seoul.

214
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:04,413
We had a huge fight before I left
for KISS, and we haven't spoken since.

215
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,832
Sorry I didn't tell you.
I didn't want you to worry.

216
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:31,023
Min Ho, why don't you tell my <i>imo-halmoni</i>
what a great teacher Jiwon is,

217
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:33,067
and how all the students love her.

218
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:37,613
As a teacher, Jiwon is so popular!

219
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:38,572
Mm.

220
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:43,703
If she had stayed in Bukjeon,
she'd have been an even better teacher!

221
00:11:43,786 --> 00:11:46,247
Don't they have kids there?

222
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:48,541
It would've been great
to have you back at home

223
00:11:48,624 --> 00:11:51,669
and see your face during the holidays.

224
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:54,922
If I went home,
I knew you'd want me to see him.

225
00:11:55,005 --> 00:11:56,215
Who?

226
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:59,510
Chung-hee? The guy she's been wanting me
to marry since I was seven

227
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:02,054
because she's always trying
to control my life.

228
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:06,475
So, Quincy, you haven't told me
how you did on your midterms.

229
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:10,855
- All A's, except AP Chem, B+.
- That's like an A.

230
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:13,858
"Like an A" is not an A.

231
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:16,861
Does it really matter?
He already has a track scholarship to USC.

232
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:19,196
Track is not exactly a major.

233
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,490
He needs to start thinking
more practically.

234
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:24,869
He's from Bukjeon,
and he has a good family,

235
00:12:24,952 --> 00:12:29,206
lots of money, and so much land!

236
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:31,917
I mean, that's great bone structure.

237
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:35,921
What? He could have a career in modeling.

238
00:12:36,005 --> 00:12:38,799
I mean, why rule out any possibilities?

239
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,177
Why didn't you wait to see
if any Ivies were interested?

240
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:42,762
She's got a point. You know,

241
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:45,473
I think it's smart
to keep your options open.

242
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:49,101
Well, I think a full ride to USC
is an incredible accomplishment.

243
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:51,771
Halmoni,
I don't care how accomplished he is.

244
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:54,398
Chung-Hee and I are nothing!

245
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,859
Marius, what are your plans
for the summer?

246
00:12:56,942 --> 00:13:00,070
Well, I'll be interning
at my dad's company.

247
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:03,866
You know, he's always talking about
handing it over to me someday. So…

248
00:13:03,949 --> 00:13:04,909
Must be nice.

249
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:07,661
Well, finally someone
around here has a decent life plan.

250
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:10,790
I mean, you can't get into medical school
just by running fast.

251
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:12,249
Okay, all due respect,

252
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,377
Q was the first person
in our entire class to get into college.

253
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:16,712
- Jin, stop.
- No!

254
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:19,757
Your son is amazing
and one of the kindest people I know.

255
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,218
Oh my God, is Jin sexy?

256
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:24,178
I am beyond proud of him.

257
00:13:24,261 --> 00:13:25,930
And you should be too.

258
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:29,600
I thought you'd get tired
of Seoul in a month,

259
00:13:29,683 --> 00:13:32,186
then come back home where you belong.

260
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:36,941
I have to live my life,
not the life you want for me.

261
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:39,151
My goodness.

262
00:13:44,448 --> 00:13:46,075
This <i>mandu </i>is delicious.

263
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,536
Yummy.

264
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:56,460
Sorry to interrupt.
Hope you're enjoying your food.

265
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:04,426
Opening a restaurant with my dad
was my mom's dream,

266
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:07,137
but she never thought we could afford it.

267
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,973
And now we can.

268
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:14,353
But really, it's our love for her
that made everything possible.

269
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:18,607
She always believed in us, no matter what.

270
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:23,571
What better way to honor her
than gathering us all here together?

271
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:25,906
My mom would be so proud.

272
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,449
Happy Chuseok!

273
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,577
Happy Chuseok!

274
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,333
Mom would be so proud of you, Dad.

275
00:14:37,501 --> 00:14:38,627
I will do my best.

276
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:43,007
At least someone's mom
would be proud of them. Must be nice!

277
00:14:56,604 --> 00:15:00,232
Jiwon, I'm so sorry. This is all my fault.

278
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:02,943
No, it's not. Uh…

279
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:05,195
Halmoni's not gonna be happy

280
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,907
unless I follow her exact plans
for my life.

281
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:09,617
I'm gonna go now.

282
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:12,953
No, uh, wait. What if I talk to her?

283
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,747
Like, matchmaker to matchmaker.

284
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:17,791
Kitty, you of all people
know how stubborn she is.

285
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:21,378
She didn't speak to her own sister
for 50 years.

286
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,423
This isn't your problem to solve.

287
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:39,730
Well, so much for checking off

288
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:42,316
a traditional family Chuseok
from my Sunset List.

289
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:45,778
In my experience,
this is how they usually end.

290
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:48,280
You still get to cross it off your list.

291
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:50,991
Well, at least I got to spend it with you.

292
00:16:02,252 --> 00:16:03,504
Min Ho!

293
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,631
Min Ho!

294
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:22,106
Are you okay?

295
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:24,984
No, they followed me
all the way from my parents' house.

296
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:28,320
That was insane. I'm gonna call my dad,
tell him we need security.

297
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:31,073
Eunice, are you okay?

298
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,118
Mm.

299
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:36,036
Oh my God, it's really you?

300
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:36,954
Mm.

301
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,789
Can I get a picture with you?

302
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:41,333
Yeah. Of course.

303
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:44,670
- Kitty, would you mind?
- Of course.

304
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:47,089
Oh, I love your necklace. Where's it from?

305
00:16:50,801 --> 00:16:54,513
- Uh, Min Ho got it for me.
- Oh, he's the best, isn't he?

306
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:02,187
It's happening. My unofficial
Eunice merch has gone viral on TikTok.

307
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:04,398
And I'm already sold out of these.

308
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:06,692
- Wow.
- Welcome to the Eunice K-Popalypse.

309
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:09,236
Ooh. Yuri, can I get a photo
of Koko with the plushie?

310
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:11,864
I'd love to create a frenzy.

311
00:17:11,947 --> 00:17:14,366
Fine, but his fee is crazy high.

312
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:15,451
Girl…

313
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:20,664
Wait. Oh my God. Oh my God.

314
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:23,250
Oh my God. Oh my God.
Oh my God, the dog is gone.

315
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:24,293
What?

316
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:25,878
Oh my God.

317
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,088
Ugh. You're so fired.

318
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:30,966
No, I cannot screw this up
for Dae and his dad. I promised.

319
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:32,926
- This night's so important for them.
- Breathe.

320
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:34,303
He has to be here somewhere.

321
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,764
- You check the back, I'll check in here.
- Okay.

322
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:38,140
Okay. Okay.

323
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:42,311
Koko! Koko! Koko! Koko!

324
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:46,023
I tried to talk to my parents about it,

325
00:17:46,106 --> 00:17:47,274
but I couldn't.

326
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,319
Honestly, I couldn't speak.

327
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:53,614
I have no idea how to begin to tell them.

328
00:17:53,697 --> 00:17:56,283
I'm so scared
they'll be disappointed in me.

329
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:58,744
What am I going to do? I'm so scared.

330
00:17:58,827 --> 00:17:59,828
No.

331
00:18:01,497 --> 00:18:02,414
Listen carefully.

332
00:18:03,457 --> 00:18:05,084
You're not alone, okay?

333
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,252
I'm responsible too.

334
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:09,338
But listen.

335
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:11,965
You can't tell anyone about this.

336
00:18:12,049 --> 00:18:14,134
If anyone finds out, we're done!

337
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:17,387
It's okay.

338
00:18:25,562 --> 00:18:28,565
Oh my God.
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

339
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:30,359
Wait. Did anyone
in the restaurant see him?

340
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:33,195
No. I lured him out
from under that table with this.

341
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:36,031
Oh no. You've given this gremlin
a taste for flesh?

342
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,533
I am so sorry.

343
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,952
Honestly, thank you so much.
I owe you big time.

344
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:41,995
If you ever need anything,
I'm your first call.

345
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:45,999
Good to know. 'Cause I'm pretty sure
you're still my emergency contact, so…

346
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:51,421
Um, will you excuse me just one second?

347
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:53,799
We need to talk.

348
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:55,968
- When did you get a dog?
- Nice necklace.

349
00:18:57,427 --> 00:19:00,305
Okay, I just overheard
the weirdest conversation…

350
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:01,723
Are you okay, Eunice?

351
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,392
Yeah.

352
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:05,477
Why wouldn't I be?

353
00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:12,234
Okay, I think you were right all along.

354
00:19:12,317 --> 00:19:14,570
Min Ho and Eunice
are definitely hiding something.

355
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:17,990
I know. He said she helped pick
this necklace. She didn't recognize it.

356
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:21,660
He said whatever it is, it's big enough
that it could end Eunice's career.

357
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:27,749
Oh no. Koko, don't eat that.
Oh no. No. Ew. Ugh.

358
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:31,044
Wait. Is this a…

359
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:33,797
A… pregnancy test.

360
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:36,884
A positive one.

361
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:42,055
What exactly did you hear them say?

362
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:46,018
See you back at the dorm.

363
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:47,186
Mm-hmm.

364
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:55,903
Kitty, you all right?

365
00:19:56,987 --> 00:19:58,530
Is Eunice pregnant?

366
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:08,457
- How did you know?
- It doesn't matter. Is it true?

367
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:10,542
Yes.

368
00:20:11,835 --> 00:20:12,836
Yes.

369
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,173
When did it happen? Over the summer?

370
00:20:16,256 --> 00:20:18,550
I don't know. When we were in Paris.

371
00:20:19,134 --> 00:20:22,679
Look, okay, no one knows, all right?
Eunice's career would be over.

372
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:24,806
My… career would be over.

373
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:28,518
I saw you two hugging last night,
and it didn't look just friendly.

374
00:20:29,561 --> 00:20:30,562
Kitty, what--

375
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:33,273
And supposedly she helped
pick out this necklace?

376
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,734
She's never even seen it before.

377
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,195
Yes, I lied about--

378
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:39,613
Yes, you did lie!

379
00:20:39,696 --> 00:20:42,491
You said you didn't hook up last summer,
and I believed you!

380
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,326
- I didn't!
- I trusted you, Min Ho!

381
00:20:46,411 --> 00:20:48,455
You got our friend pregnant?

382
00:20:48,538 --> 00:20:50,832
Friend pregnant?
What are you talking about?

383
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,334
Who are you?

384
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:56,046
Kitty!

385
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:05,347
Hey, want a mocktail?

386
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:08,141
You okay? What happened?

387
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:11,687
Min Ho said that he didn't hook up with
anyone last summer, but he was lying.

388
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:16,233
And not just about that.
I don't know if I can get over this.

389
00:21:16,316 --> 00:21:19,236
I'm so sorry.
I don't know if I could either.

390
00:21:19,319 --> 00:21:21,655
How'd you get over
what happened with Q and Marius?

391
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:24,408
- I mean, it's not the same, but…
- What are you talking about?

392
00:21:27,035 --> 00:21:28,912
- Never mind.
- Kitty?

393
00:21:30,872 --> 00:21:32,165
No, Jin, wait! I…

394
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:35,085
What happened between you and Marius?

395
00:21:35,168 --> 00:21:37,629
- What do you mean?
- Kitty told me something happened.

396
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,844
- Okay, it's not a big deal.
- Tell me what happened, Q.

397
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:45,387
Jin, please, not right now.

398
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:46,430
Tell me!

399
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:51,810
It was before you came to USC,
and it was stupid. It was just a photo.

400
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:54,813
You know what they say.
A picture's worth a thousand words.

401
00:21:54,896 --> 00:21:56,106
Jin, wait! Wait, don't--

402
00:21:57,774 --> 00:21:59,192
Oh my God.

403
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:05,282
Oh! Oh my God, I'm so sorry.
Are you okay? Oh my God, I'm so sorry.

404
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:09,494
Jin! What is wrong with you?
He only sent me one picture!

405
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:13,081
You?

406
00:22:15,834 --> 00:22:16,793
Quin…

407
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:18,837
Jin. Jin, wait.

408
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,344
Jin, wait. Can we please just talk?

409
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:28,430
I thought that you told him.

410
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:30,974
I didn't think I had
to worry about you bringing it up!

411
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:34,895
- I didn't think it'd be a big deal if--
- Kitty, just stay away from me!

412
00:22:59,961 --> 00:23:03,715
So, I guess Marius was
more than just your roommate?

413
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,223
I don't even know why I sent that pic.

414
00:23:11,306 --> 00:23:12,849
Jin loves me,

415
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:14,226
and I love him.

416
00:23:15,143 --> 00:23:17,813
Marius has been playing games
since the day we met.

417
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:21,983
Well, my doctorate
isn't in psychology, but…

418
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:23,819
maybe there's a reason

419
00:23:23,902 --> 00:23:26,780
why you're attracted to people
who don't treat you so well.

420
00:23:31,284 --> 00:23:35,747
You know, I failed my, uh, chem final,
first year of college.

421
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:39,376
Yeah. I stayed in bed all week.

422
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:42,254
You never told me that.

423
00:23:42,337 --> 00:23:44,131
The pressure got to me.

424
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:49,302
Being pre-med,
being my immigrant parents' only child.

425
00:23:49,386 --> 00:23:52,139
I mean, they never told me
they were proud of me.

426
00:23:52,222 --> 00:23:56,268
I guess they were afraid
I would stop trying.

427
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:09,573
I don't always show it,
but, um, for the record,

428
00:24:10,824 --> 00:24:15,203
your whole life,
I've never not been proud of you.

429
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,293
Even tonight?

430
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,045
Even tonight.

431
00:24:25,338 --> 00:24:29,468
And I am so sorry
if I made you feel otherwise.

432
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:31,553
But Jin…

433
00:24:32,721 --> 00:24:35,807
Jin cares more about you
than what I think of him.

434
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:37,476
And that's…

435
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:40,061
That's the kind of love you deserve.

436
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:44,274
Come here.

437
00:24:49,029 --> 00:24:51,823
So, you think Min Ho and Eunice hooked up?

438
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:55,827
- He said it happened in Paris.
- That's impossible.

439
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:58,580
I'm sorry to be the one to tell you this.

440
00:24:58,663 --> 00:25:01,750
I know how you feel about her,
so I felt like you deserved to know.

441
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:04,878
No, I mean,
it's, like, literally impossible.

442
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:07,964
I was with Eunice
the whole time she was in Paris.

443
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:09,841
What? What are you talking about?

444
00:25:09,925 --> 00:25:11,635
When the settlement came through,

445
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:14,804
my dad gave me some
to spend on whatever I wanted.

446
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:17,682
So I bought a plane ticket
and surprised Eunice.

447
00:25:17,766 --> 00:25:20,477
And Min Ho doesn't know that. Nobody does.

448
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,021
Did you sleep with her?

449
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:27,108
I'm sorry. It's not my business, but…

450
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:29,486
Right now, this is important.

451
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:37,869
Yes, I did.

452
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:39,746
But after we came back to school,

453
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:42,165
she started acting
like it never even happened.

454
00:25:42,249 --> 00:25:43,833
Oh my God.

455
00:25:44,417 --> 00:25:46,253
Min Ho is protecting her.

456
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:48,463
Protecting her? From what?

457
00:25:50,131 --> 00:25:52,884
I'm sorry. I can't tell you.

458
00:25:52,968 --> 00:25:56,096
But I do think you need to talk to Eunice.

459
00:25:56,846 --> 00:25:59,516
I don't know.

460
00:25:59,599 --> 00:26:02,227
She's too much of a big star now.

461
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:06,147
People saw one paparazzi photo
of her coming into this place,

462
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:08,692
and now we're booked out for a month.

463
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:11,486
Wow, that's great news
for you and your dad.

464
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:15,865
But regarding Eunice…

465
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:20,620
sometimes things are
more complicated than they seem.

466
00:26:24,749 --> 00:26:26,960
Whatever it is, you can tell me.

467
00:26:28,712 --> 00:26:31,840
Honestly, after Paris…

468
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:34,634
I stopped having my period.

469
00:26:35,594 --> 00:26:39,556
Min Ho thinks I was with Tae-Oh,

470
00:26:39,639 --> 00:26:42,350
but obviously I was only with you.

471
00:26:45,687 --> 00:26:48,732
If you're saying
what I think you're saying,

472
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:51,693
let's do this together.

473
00:26:52,527 --> 00:26:54,487
We can even get married if we need to.

474
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:57,782
No, Dae, it's not like that.

475
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:00,994
I'm not pregnant.

476
00:27:01,077 --> 00:27:02,203
Are you sure?

477
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:03,163
Mm.

478
00:27:03,246 --> 00:27:09,544
For a while, I thought that I was.

479
00:27:10,211 --> 00:27:11,671
But that wasn't the case.

480
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:16,551
When I came home tonight,

481
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:18,970
I started my period.

482
00:27:20,513 --> 00:27:22,265
I guess I was so stressed.

483
00:27:24,476 --> 00:27:30,523
The paparazzi always following me,
fans always wanting something from me…

484
00:27:31,191 --> 00:27:34,319
Honestly, I was so scared.

485
00:27:35,779 --> 00:27:37,614
I felt like I couldn't breathe.

486
00:27:38,406 --> 00:27:40,617
Dae, I just

487
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:45,997
want to go back
to the way things used to be.

488
00:28:02,389 --> 00:28:03,390
Hi.

489
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:15,276
I'm sorry.

490
00:28:17,070 --> 00:28:19,948
I got everything so wrong.

491
00:28:21,616 --> 00:28:23,493
Why did you not just tell me the truth?

492
00:28:24,661 --> 00:28:26,705
Because I gave Eunice my word.

493
00:28:27,789 --> 00:28:31,292
I didn't expect my own girlfriend
would believe the worst of me.

494
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:33,461
I know.

495
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:37,340
I think that I spent my whole summer

496
00:28:38,675 --> 00:28:43,805
watching you with all these fancy people,
and doing these fancy things,

497
00:28:44,472 --> 00:28:49,102
and it made me question if I would

498
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:56,109
ever really fit… in your big, fancy world.

499
00:28:58,403 --> 00:29:00,155
So I got in my head.

500
00:29:00,238 --> 00:29:03,950
Like you did with Gigi.
Like you did with Marius.

501
00:29:05,493 --> 00:29:07,495
You know, I get it now.

502
00:29:09,414 --> 00:29:11,499
It's not that you don't trust me.

503
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:16,004
It's that you've never trusted me.

504
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:17,464
No, no, that's not true--

505
00:29:17,547 --> 00:29:21,426
I've done everything…
to show you how I feel about you.

506
00:29:22,510 --> 00:29:26,473
I've given you every reason
for you to believe in me.

507
00:29:28,683 --> 00:29:30,560
But the problem isn't me, it's you.

508
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:37,358
We're done.

509
00:29:37,442 --> 00:29:39,360
No, I…

510
00:29:39,444 --> 00:29:40,570
Min Ho…

511
00:29:42,405 --> 00:29:44,616
<i>Please record your message.</i>

512
00:29:44,699 --> 00:29:49,204
LJ. I need to talk to you.

513
00:29:50,538 --> 00:29:52,624
I've messed everything up.

514
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:57,003
I don't know what to do.

515
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:16,272
<i>It's killing me</i>

516
00:30:17,565 --> 00:30:20,193
<i>Fear is holding me down</i>

517
00:30:21,694 --> 00:30:26,199
<i>But I wanna be sure</i>

518
00:30:57,313 --> 00:31:01,109
<i>I will burst through the crowd</i>

519
00:31:01,818 --> 00:31:05,321
<i>Screaming for this man</i>

520
00:31:05,405 --> 00:31:11,244
<i>If I got this with you</i>

